4 Raro sacrificantes. This use of the verb sacrzficare—to sacrifice—as well as (fferre, along with the nouns sacerdos and altaria, affords proof how, in the British Church of the sixth century, that idea of the Eucharist as the highest act of worship, sacrificial worship, which found form and expression in other lands, at that time and subsequently, was the prevalent one. These terms are not used by Gildas in any figurative or metaphorical sense.
